description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse – RGN, Band 5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KENT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; PRISONS (Forensic &amp; Prisons Directorate, Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A number of posts across H&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MP Cookham Wood Primary Healthcare Services and HMP Rochester&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust provides integrated primary healthcare services in HMP Cookham and HMP Rochester. You will be joining the team at a great time as we are securing our reputation as a high performing organisation within Prisons locally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our aim:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“To provide each prisoner with access to NHS services equivalent to those available to the general public. It is, however recognised that maintaining security for all prisoners is of paramount importance as well as meeting the safety and welfare needs of staff undertaking these health care provisions.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust looking for RGNs, preferably with experience of working in a Primary Care/Acute care setting on a full time basis. Our services include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Primary care nursing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Long Term conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minor injuries and Illness’&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Emergency care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health assessment and Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellman/woman clinics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a Multi-Disciplinary Team who support GP services, Optometry, Podiatry, Physiotherapy, Sexual Health and mental health services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We take pride in our staff and recognise the skills, knowledge and how their competencies directly impacts on the quality of services received by patients. The trust is therefore committed to investing in your ongoing CPD development.Benefits include flexible working, lease car and cycle to work scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Comfort Onwuchekwa, Deputy Operational Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;c.onwuchekwa@nhs.net 01634 823318&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact c.onwuchekwa@nhs.net or antony.hawkins@nhs.net for further details&lt;/p&gt;
